{"TopicId":187301,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Change Navball Orientation","CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T00:07:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T00:07:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt used to be there... but I\u0027m missing the button to change the orientation of the navball.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve crawl through the menu options but I don\u0027t find something that fits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T00:15:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEsc -\u0026gt; Settings -\u0026gt; Scroll all the way down.\u00A0 Last slider.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis must be done\u003Cem\u003E in flight\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaerbanogue","CreatedById":189143,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T12:57:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to change the navball size and position on HUD go on settings as indicated by @Geonovast\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223652637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566173730\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEsc -\u0026gt; Settings -\u0026gt; Scroll all the way down.\u00A0 Last slider.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need to change the orientation of the navball from a reference point (orbit, target, surface) click on the upper part of the navball where is displayed your relative speed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen if your navball is oriented like on a 90\u00B0plan or is facing down, you need to right-click on your pod and switch between control points\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope it\u0027ll help\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T17:04:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose I\u0027ve got. And neither what I\u0027m looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe was/is a button available that when you clicked on it would cycle through, normal, reversed, forward, and would change the \u0022zero\u0022 point of the nav-ball.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKind of found it. It is the button \u0022control point\u0022 but it only appears to be available on probe cores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-19T17:13:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/19/2019 05:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by steuben\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T17:40:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223652977\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566234267\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277368\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steuben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, steuben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKind of found it. It is the button \u0022control point\u0022 but it only appears to be available on probe cores.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should also show up on all command pods and docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T19:16:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t show on the Mk2 Cockpit or the clamp-o-tron port. But does on the Mk1-3 pod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-19T22:47:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ddb570de-8863-4f86-b380-f144178c4ac7_tex\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002254.50\u0022 height=\u0022218\u0022 width=\u0022400\u0022 src=\u0022https://y.yarn.co/ddb570de-8863-4f86-b380-f144178c4ac7_text_hi.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T00:32:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223652997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566236419\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt should also show up on all command pods and docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about should or all, but it does show up on some.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223653125\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566242195\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277368\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steuben\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, steuben said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoesn\u0027t show on the Mk2 Cockpit or the clamp-o-tron port. But does on the Mk1-3 pod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could see not adding it to plane cockpits or docking ports. UI clutter is bad enough that you really need to think about how often a button is going to be used. Wanting to control a cockpit from the front because when landed it\u0027s a rover is one thing, wanting to control a docking port or airplane backwards is another... with a lot fewer use cases.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223653693\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022187301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566254832\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ddb570de-8863-4f86-b380-f144178c4ac7_tex\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002254.50\u0022 height=\u0022218\u0022 width=\u0022400\u0022 src=\u0022https://y.yarn.co/ddb570de-8863-4f86-b380-f144178c4ac7_text_hi.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe we have no bug here, but instead a misunderstanding of the feature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-20T01:25:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, I see my confusion.\u00A0 I was thinking \u0022Control from here\u0022.\u00A0 I know what you\u0027re talking about now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}